$. When we raise $-1$ to an odd power, we get $-1$, so $\\left(-345\\right)^{6}$ is $-$ $3,389,294,561$. When we raise $-1$ to even number , we get $1$, so $\\left(\\left(\\left(-345\\right)^{6}\\right)^{2}\\right)^{0}=1.$ We have now shown that $\\left(\\left(-345\\right)^{4}\\right)^{2}$ is 3,389,294,561.  So, $\\left(\\left(\\left(\\left(\\left(-345\\right)^{4}\\right)^{2}\\right)^{0}\\right)^{-2}\\right)^{-4}$ is $\\left(\\left(3,389,294,561\\right)^{-2}\\right)^{-4}$. $\\left(3,389,294,561\\right)^{-2}$ is equivalent to $\\frac{1}{ 3,389,294,561 ^{2}}$, so $\\left(\\left(3,389,294,561\\right)^{-2}\\right)^{-4}$ is $\\left(\\frac{1}{ 3,389,294,561 ^{2}}\\right)^{-4}$.  $\\left(\\frac{1}{3,389,294,561 ^{2}}\\right)^{-4}$ is equivalent to $ 3,389,294,561^{8}$, which is $ $ $2.0 32 859 136 249 324$.$</think> <answer> $2.032859136249324$ </answer>", "truth": "1", "reward_format": 1.0, "reward_answer": 0.0, "reward_total": 0.0}, {"prompt": "A conversation between User and Assistant. The User asks a question, and the Assistant solves it. The Assistant first thinks about the reasoning process in the mind and then provides the User with the answer. The reasoning process is enclosed within <think> </think> and answer is enclosed within <answer> </answer> tags, respectively, i.e., <think> reasoning process here </think> <answer> answer here </answer>.\nUser: What is $\\left(\\dfrac{7}{16}\\right)^{111}\\times \\left(\\dfrac{16}{7}\\right)^{111}$?\nAssistant: <think>", "response": " \nThe expression $\\left(\\dfrac{7}{16}\\right)^{111}\\times \\left(\\dfrac{16}{7}\\right)^{111}$ can be simplified by observing that $\\dfrac{7}{16}$ and $\\dfrac{16}{7}$ are reciprocals. When you multiply a number by its reciprocal, you are essentially multiplying $\\dfrac{7}{16}$ by $\\dfrac{16}{7}$, which results in 1. Therefore, raising this product to any power will still result in 1.\n </think> <answer>\n1\n </answer>", "truth": "1", "reward_format": 1.0, "reward_answer": 1.0, "reward_to